# HELP ---------------------
# 0=READY gitignore sets
#   https://github.com/github/gitignore/tree/main
# 1=NESTING
#   (*.xyz) or the same (**/*.xyz) - files in any nested directory!
#   (*xyz/) or the same (**/*xyz/) same as for directories
# 2=CaseSense!
#   Linux/Mac-Sensitive!
#   Windows - INSensitive!
#   TRICKS
#       CORRECT: *.so => *.[Ss][Oo]
#       WRONG: one line with SPACING ===> *.so/ *.SO/ *.So/ -> will exclude exact names with spaces "*.so/ *.SO/ *.So/"
#   BUT in real life many global static folders uses only one register!
# 3=SLASH_ENDS not need but if used applyed only for directories!
#   (*xyz) - both for directories and files
#   (*xyz/) - only for directories
# 4=UNIGNORE=keep special files in ignored folder
#   .vscode/*
#   !.vscode/settings.json
#   !.vscode/tasks.json
# 5=CHECKS
#   git check-ignore -v path/to/file
#   git status --ignored

